Guilty - German tennis great Boris Becker was found guilty of four charges relating to his 2017 bankruptcy trial LONDON - Former Wimbledon champion Boris Becker was found guilty of four charges relating to his 2017 bankruptcy on Friday. READ:Â Jurors retire in trial of former tennis star Boris Becker The 54-year-old German was accused of hiding millions of pounds worth of assets, including two Wimbledon trophies, to avoid paying his debts. A London court found him guilty of removal of property, two counts of failing to disclose estate and concealing debt and acquitted him on a further 20 counts. Becker, who has lived in Britain since 2012, was bailed ahead of sentencing at the same court on 29 April.